; 01/07/2026.
; 
; Added another two steps to "03_dremel_grinder_draw_square.ngc".
;
; Before starting drawing the square, after the spindle reaches full
; speed, plunge Z-Axis down by 2 machine units.
;
; After finishing drawing, retract the Z-Axis up to the 0 position 
; before stopping the spindle, this is safe, preventing the tool 
; getting stuck or being dragged.
;
; G90 is Absolute mode, "plunge down" must be a negative value.

(--- Setup and Safety Codes ---)
G21          (Set units to Millimeters)
G90          (Set to Absolute Distance Mode)
G17          (Select the X-Y plane)
G40          (Cancel tool radius compensation)
G49          (Cancel tool length offset)

(--- Starting the Test Square ---)
(Ensure we start at the origin at a controlled feedrate)
G0 X0 Y0 Z0   (Rapid move to the origin)
G1 F300       (Set linear interpolation movement speed to 300 mm/min)

M3 S1000      (Enable spindle)
( Gemini optimisation )
G4 P3         (Wait 3 seconds for spindle to reach full speed)

(--- Plunge Z-Axis ---)
G1 Z-2       (Move Z-axis down 2 units into the material)

(1. Move from origin to X 50)
G1 X50 Y0

(2. From X 50, Y 0, move to Y 50)
G1 X50 Y50

(3. From X 50, Y 50, move back to X 0, Y 50)
G1 X0 Y50

(4. From X 0, Y 50, move back to X 0, Y 0)
G1 X0 Y0

(--- Retract Z-Axis before turning off spindle ---)
G1 Z0        (Bring Z-axis back up to safe starting height)

M5            (Stop spindle)

(--- Program End ---)
M2           (End of program)
